import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="origin", y="count", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    chart.axhline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    chart.set(xlabel='Origin', ylabel='Flight Count')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between different origins?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))
    sns.barplot(x='destination', y='count', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between different destinations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Flight Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.pivot("origin", "destination", "count")
    ax = sns.heatmap(data, cmap="YlGnBu", annot=True, fmt=".0f", linewidths=.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Destination')
    ax.set_ylabel('Origin')
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights between different origins and destinations?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of flight counts over time?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Flight Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
